The names of six soldiers who died in Odessa on March 6 have appeared.

Their names are published by the Veterans Hub Odesa organization.

The cause of death is not specified, but their list includes Yuriy Slepchenko, who, as previously reported on social networks, died during a Russian attack on the port on March 6, when Zelensky arrived in Odessa.

Veterans Hub Odesa publishes the names of 6 dead sailors:

- Chief Petty Officer Stanislav Khokhlov (08/28/1997 - 03/06/2024);

- Petty Officer 2nd class Vyacheslav Vasiliev (04/11/1992 - 03/06/2024);

- junior sergeant Vladimir Butov (04/15/1988 - 03/06/2024);

- senior sailor Yuri Slepchenko (09.09.1986 - 06.03.2024);

- sailor Pyotr Kornienko (02/11/1998 - 03/06/2024);

- sailor Andrey Likhno (03/12/1996 - 03/06/2024). Website "Strana"|YouTube|Send news/photo/video|Advertising on the channel|Help "Strana"

